# Update Overview

## Goal
Refresh `wiki/overview.md` so it accurately reflects the current state of the {{config.project.name}} wiki — Key Themes, Open Questions, Evolving Synthesis, and Statistics. The overview is a living document, not a static introduction; it must keep pace with what the wiki actually contains.

## Core Principle
The overview is the wiki's executive summary for both humans and agents. It is the page a new reader (or a fresh agent session) reads first to orient themselves. When it drifts out of sync with the wiki's actual content, every downstream operation suffers. This skill is the resync.

The ingest workflow already touches overview as part of every ingestion. Invoke this skill directly when:
- You want an overview pass without ingesting a new source (after a batch of edits, a query session, or a lint pass)
- The overview feels stale relative to the wiki
- The Statistics section is wrong
- New themes have emerged across pages that aren't reflected here

<workflow>

<step n="1" goal="Read the current overview">
  <action>Read `wiki/overview.md` in full</action>
  <action>Note the existing Key Themes, Open Questions, and Evolving Synthesis sections</action>
  <action>Note the current Statistics — these are about to be recomputed</action>
</step>

<step n="2" goal="Survey the wiki's actual state">
  <action>Read `wiki/index.md` to get the catalog of all pages</action>
  <action>Count pages by type: entities in `wiki/entities/`, concepts in `wiki/concepts/`, sources in `wiki/sources/`, comparisons in `wiki/comparisons/`</action>
  <action>Skim entity and concept pages with the highest `source_count` — those are the most-supported claims in the wiki and most likely to reflect real themes</action>
  <action>Scan `wiki/log.md` since the overview's `last_updated` date — what has been added, updated, or flagged?</action>
  <action>Identify pages with `confidence: disputed` or `status: superseded` — these belong in the overview's nuance, not its main synthesis</action>
</step>

<step n="3" goal="Recompute the Statistics section">
  <action>Update the Statistics section of `wiki/overview.md` with current counts:</action>
  <action>- Total pages (sum across all wiki subdirectories, excluding overview/index/log)</action>
  <action>- Entities count</action>
  <action>- Concepts count</action>
  <action>- Sources ingested count</action>
  <action>- Comparisons count</action>
  <action>- Last updated: today's ISO date</action>
</step>

<step n="4" goal="Refresh Key Themes">
  <action>Identify themes that have emerged or strengthened — patterns that appear across multiple pages with strong source backing</action>
  <action>Each theme is 1-2 sentences describing the pattern, with {{config.wiki.cross_ref_style}} links to the entity/concept pages where it shows up</action>
  <action>Remove themes that no longer reflect the wiki's content (e.g., the pages supporting them have been superseded or merged away)</action>
  <action>Preserve nuance — do not flatten contested themes into majority positions; if a theme is disputed, say so</action>
</step>

<step n="5" goal="Refresh Open Questions">
  <action>Read existing Open Questions. For each, check whether the wiki has accumulated enough material to answer it</action>
  <check if="a question has been substantively answered by recent ingestions or filed answers">
    <action>Check it off and link to the page(s) that answered it</action>
  </check>
  <action>Add new open questions surfaced by recent activity: gaps in coverage, contradictions worth resolving, threads worth pulling on</action>
  <action>Prefer specific questions over vague ones — "What is the impact of X on Y?" beats "What about X?"</action>
</step>

<step n="6" goal="Refresh Evolving Synthesis">
  <action>Rewrite (or revise in place) the Evolving Synthesis section to reflect what the wiki currently knows</action>
  <action>Structure it around: what we know with high confidence, what remains uncertain or disputed, how the pieces connect, what the emerging picture looks like</action>
  <action>This is a living summary — it should READ like the wiki's current best understanding, not a chronology of how it got here</action>
  <action>Do not introduce knowledge that is not present in the wiki — synthesis here must be wiki-backed</action>
</step>

<step n="7" goal="Log the refresh">
  <action>Append to `wiki/log.md`:</action>
  <action>Format: `## [ISO-timestamp] update-overview | Refreshed overview`</action>
  <action>Include a brief summary: themes added/removed, questions checked off, questions added, page counts</action>
</step>

<step n="8" goal="Report">
  <action>Tell the user what changed in the overview and what they should look at</action>
  <action>If new Open Questions were added, suggest which ones might be the most productive to investigate next</action>
  <action>If themes shifted meaningfully, point that out — it usually means the wiki has matured into a new phase</action>
</step>

</workflow>
